WEBVTT

00:40.499 --> 00:43.491
[ANIMALS CALLING AND CHITTERING]

00:55.222 --> 00:58.760
NARRATOR:
The ancient forests of North America.

01:01.937 --> 01:03.553
Mysterious...

01:04.105 --> 01:05.266
...wild...

01:05.774 --> 01:07.981
...a world of giants...

01:08.777 --> 01:12.270
...where great bears and wolves prowl.

01:25.002 --> 01:26.868
But hidden in the shadows...

01:27.129 --> 01:30.667
...there is a miniature,
almost magical world.

01:34.720 --> 01:38.714
A place where nothing
is quite as it seems.

01:52.904 --> 01:56.898
The home of extraordinary,
tiny creatures.

02:04.207 --> 02:05.948
It's fall.

02:06.543 --> 02:08.375
And the moment one little chipmunk...

02:08.628 --> 02:10.495
...has been waiting for.

02:14.926 --> 02:16.587
The arrival...

02:17.262 --> 02:19.629
...of acorns.

02:22.142 --> 02:23.507
[CROAKS]

02:25.354 --> 02:27.140
When you're just 6 inches tall...

02:27.397 --> 02:29.889
...the world looks very different.

02:37.908 --> 02:40.320
This chipmunk is only <i>2</i> months old...

02:40.577 --> 02:42.409
...and is already facing what will be...

02:42.663 --> 02:44.870
...the greatest challenge of his life.

02:53.548 --> 02:55.585
He has to collect enough acorns...

02:55.842 --> 02:58.300
...to get him through the coming winter.

03:15.070 --> 03:17.732
He'll need at least a hundred...

03:17.989 --> 03:19.946
...so every acorn counts.

03:55.485 --> 03:56.896
[CROAKS]

04:07.497 --> 04:09.113
He will only survive
the coming winter...

04:09.916 --> 04:12.157
...by escaping underground.

04:19.259 --> 04:22.502
But he can't hibernate like a bear.

04:22.763 --> 04:25.972
His body is too small
to store enough fat.

04:26.475 --> 04:27.215
Instead...

04:27.476 --> 04:29.387
...he needs a store of food.

04:39.863 --> 04:41.570
For his first year...

04:41.823 --> 04:43.814
...the youngster's done well.

04:46.578 --> 04:48.410
But he's being watched.

04:48.663 --> 04:49.994
[CHIRPS]

04:59.674 --> 05:02.086
This is an older chipmunk...

05:02.344 --> 05:05.553
...worldly wise and sneakier too.

05:15.232 --> 05:18.520
Older chipmunks are notorious thieves.

05:29.538 --> 05:32.030
After all, why work...

05:32.290 --> 05:34.247
...when you can steal
from someone else?

05:43.093 --> 05:46.302
For the youngster,
life without his store of acorns...

05:46.555 --> 05:48.796
...will spell disaster.

05:53.937 --> 05:56.304
But he isn't the only little creature...

05:56.565 --> 06:00.559
...struggling to grow up
in the big, wide world.

06:08.618 --> 06:10.859
On the other side of the continent...

06:11.121 --> 06:13.783
...lies one of the harshest environments
on Earth.

06:46.865 --> 06:49.448
The Sonoran Desert...

06:51.286 --> 06:54.244
...in America's wild west.

06:55.332 --> 06:58.245
A place of legend.

07:03.214 --> 07:05.171
For the first human settlers...

07:05.425 --> 07:09.419
...survival in this unforgiving desert
was on a knife edge.

07:14.893 --> 07:17.180
So imagine how hard it must be...

07:17.437 --> 07:21.021
...if you stand only 3 inches tall.

07:32.994 --> 07:36.112
A tiny grasshopper mouse.

07:43.672 --> 07:44.878
This caring mother...

07:45.131 --> 07:49.045
...was left to raise
four hungry mouths alone.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.838
[SQUEAKING]

07:53.807 --> 07:56.765
They're not yet ready
to make it on their own.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.386
Except for one.

08:01.106 --> 08:03.222
The eldest son is bolder...

08:03.483 --> 08:07.272
...and increasingly drawn
by the call of the wild.

08:08.154 --> 08:10.361
[ANIMAL HOWLING IN DISTANCE]

08:21.543 --> 08:25.127
Every night, his mother
goes out to find food.

08:28.216 --> 08:31.880
Hiding in the shadows
is a host of enemies.

08:33.722 --> 08:35.884
Giant enemies.

08:57.620 --> 09:00.829
There are more
venomous creatures here...

09:01.082 --> 09:03.540
...than anywhere else in the U.S.A.

09:11.051 --> 09:13.543
No place for the timid.

09:27.817 --> 09:30.525
But she's not your average mouse.

09:44.334 --> 09:47.201
It's why old-timers call her...

09:47.462 --> 09:49.078
...by an earlier name:

09:52.425 --> 09:54.587
Scorpion mouse.

09:56.221 --> 09:57.336
[SQUEAKING]

09:59.849 --> 10:03.058
The sting of a scorpion
can kill a human...

10:03.311 --> 10:06.520
...but a scorpion mouse
has a superpower.

10:10.527 --> 10:13.019
Her body is immune to the venom.

10:13.363 --> 10:14.774
[SQUEAKS]

10:16.449 --> 10:20.238
She specializes
in hunting deadly prey.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.415
[HOWLING]

10:28.002 --> 10:29.208
To defend her territory...

10:29.462 --> 10:32.295
...she stakes a claim
with a warning howl.

10:50.275 --> 10:53.393
This young scorpion mouse
has a lot...

10:53.653 --> 10:54.734
...to live up to.

10:58.616 --> 11:02.610
He knows nothing
of the dangers outside his door.

11:06.583 --> 11:08.665
But barely 3 weeks old...

11:08.918 --> 11:12.912
...growing curiosity means
he's about to face them.

11:32.358 --> 11:34.065
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

12:01.971 --> 12:03.712
Back in the wild wood...

12:03.973 --> 12:07.967
...the young chipmunk is still preparing
for the coming winter...

12:16.653 --> 12:20.647
...unaware that his store
is being ransacked.

12:37.882 --> 12:40.715
For the thief,
it's a dash back home...

12:45.974 --> 12:46.805
...to stock up...

12:47.058 --> 12:48.344
...his own store...

12:54.107 --> 12:58.101
...before heading straight back
to the scene of the crime.

13:25.054 --> 13:29.048
Out in the woods, the young chipmunk
is about to face a new problem...

13:29.767 --> 13:32.259
...and this one's a giant.

13:33.688 --> 13:35.804
[HOOF STEPS APPROACH]

13:40.278 --> 13:41.768
[BELLOWING]

13:51.080 --> 13:54.994
This half-ton moose
is hungry for acorns too.

13:56.627 --> 13:57.742
[CHIRPING]

14:12.185 --> 14:14.017
[CHIRPS]

14:19.984 --> 14:21.770
Arriving back at his burrow...

14:22.028 --> 14:25.896
...the young chipmunk
is in for another surprise.

14:33.206 --> 14:37.074
His store is now almost empty.

14:40.296 --> 14:41.786
And that's not all.

14:49.555 --> 14:51.717
The burglar is back...

14:51.974 --> 14:53.464
...and he's a seasoned...

14:53.726 --> 14:54.887
...fighter.

14:56.771 --> 14:58.762
[CHIPMUNKS TRILLING]

15:10.868 --> 15:11.858
An older...

15:12.120 --> 15:14.828
...stronger chipmunk
can kill a youngster.

15:17.959 --> 15:18.949
[SQUEALS]

15:23.589 --> 15:25.250
All he can do is run...

15:25.508 --> 15:26.873
...for his life.

15:33.641 --> 15:35.973
And without a store of acorns...

15:36.227 --> 15:39.185
...how will he survive
the coming winter?

15:42.150 --> 15:43.891
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

16:05.339 --> 16:07.376
In the Sonoran Desert...

16:07.633 --> 16:09.169
...the young grasshopper mouse...

16:09.427 --> 16:12.294
...faces his first night out alone.

16:28.237 --> 16:30.069
[RATTLING]

16:41.167 --> 16:44.455
There are more rattlesnakes here
than anywhere else...

16:44.712 --> 16:46.077
...on Earth.

17:35.429 --> 17:36.419
[HISSING]

17:37.181 --> 17:38.546
[SQUEALS]

18:01.956 --> 18:05.574
The mouse's superfast reactions
have saved him.

18:10.381 --> 18:14.375
But he still has a lot to learn
about the dangers of the desert.

18:19.140 --> 18:23.134
For the moment,
a dry riverbed seems a safe refuge.

18:35.448 --> 18:39.316
But tonight,
a powerful force threatens.

18:41.078 --> 18:42.694
One so rare...

18:42.955 --> 18:45.913
...a mouse could go its whole life
without seeing it.

19:02.058 --> 19:03.469
When the rain arrives...

19:04.101 --> 19:07.969
...a year's worth
can fall in a single night.

19:30.294 --> 19:33.537
Small animals lose heat
faster than big ones...

19:33.798 --> 19:35.960
...and if he's not careful,
his wet fur...

19:36.217 --> 19:38.549
...could lead to a fatal chill.

20:16.632 --> 20:18.999
Months of blazing sun...

20:19.260 --> 20:23.254
...have baked Arizona's earth
as hard as stone.

20:25.349 --> 20:27.966
The water can't soak away.

20:28.602 --> 20:31.469
Instead, it gathers momentum...

20:31.731 --> 20:34.348
...as it races downhill.

20:36.986 --> 20:38.772
[SQUEAKING]

21:51.435 --> 21:53.346
In the northern woods...

21:53.604 --> 21:56.892
...winter is just a breath away.

22:16.085 --> 22:18.201
Once the freeze sets in...

22:18.462 --> 22:20.578
...the young chipmunk
won't last a week...

22:20.840 --> 22:23.081
...without a store of acorns.

22:27.346 --> 22:30.384
And the days are getting shorter.

22:52.997 --> 22:56.115
The urgent need
to replace his stolen store...

22:56.375 --> 22:59.493
...forces him into unknown territory.

23:04.341 --> 23:05.672
[PANTING]

23:11.849 --> 23:14.932
The sound is irresistible.

23:34.371 --> 23:36.203
[CHIRPS]

23:42.254 --> 23:45.747
This is the home of a silent hunter.

23:48.928 --> 23:51.420
A great horned owl.

23:51.680 --> 23:54.968
Over 20 times
the size of the chipmunk.

24:21.835 --> 24:23.166
[CHIRPS]

24:27.257 --> 24:28.418
[HOOTS]

24:44.483 --> 24:46.315
[HOOTS]

25:12.970 --> 25:14.836
[SCREECHES]

25:32.364 --> 25:33.604
[SHRIEKS]

25:37.244 --> 25:38.029
[SCREECHES]

25:50.424 --> 25:51.710
[TRILLS]

25:54.720 --> 25:55.881
[CALLS]

25:59.266 --> 26:00.882
[CHIRPS]

26:07.149 --> 26:08.731
He may have escaped...

26:08.984 --> 26:10.145
...but his store...

26:10.402 --> 26:13.440
...is still almost empty.

26:37.805 --> 26:40.968
High noon in the wild west.

26:49.650 --> 26:52.358
So hot, the last drop of rain...

26:52.611 --> 26:54.352
...is long gone.

26:56.907 --> 27:00.070
The highest temperatures
are down at mouse level...

27:00.327 --> 27:01.988
...where it can reach a blistering...

27:02.246 --> 27:05.364
...140 degrees Fahrenheit.

27:23.809 --> 27:25.140
It's a side of the desert...

27:25.394 --> 27:28.762
...a nocturnal mouse should never see.

27:29.690 --> 27:33.183
Except for those washed up,
exhausted...

27:33.443 --> 27:36.561
...and swept very far from home.

27:49.751 --> 27:51.162
[SNIFFING]

28:00.637 --> 28:01.877
In daytime...

28:02.139 --> 28:05.973
...the desert
is a real-life Jurassic Park...

28:09.688 --> 28:13.226
...where heat brings giants to life.

28:20.782 --> 28:24.070
But this realm of reptiles is ruled...

28:24.328 --> 28:25.864
...from the air.

28:26.205 --> 28:27.695
[SQUAWKING]

28:36.173 --> 28:37.914
Harris hawks.

28:42.846 --> 28:44.678
"Eyes like a hawk"...

28:44.932 --> 28:46.764
...is no empty phrase.

28:49.019 --> 28:51.511
Their vision is thought to be
eight times...

28:51.772 --> 28:53.604
...as good as ours.

28:59.696 --> 29:00.401
They're the only...

29:00.697 --> 29:03.564
...birds of prey that hunt in packs.

29:26.932 --> 29:27.888
It's hard to outwit...

29:28.392 --> 29:29.348
...this intelligent...

29:29.601 --> 29:30.591
...team.

29:30.852 --> 29:32.092
[SQUAWKING]

29:44.116 --> 29:45.732
[HAWK CONTINUES SQUAWKING]

30:04.177 --> 30:05.417
Long feather-free...

30:05.679 --> 30:06.293
...legs...

30:06.555 --> 30:08.796
...are ideal for extracting mice...

30:09.057 --> 30:10.889
...from those hard-to-reach places.

30:12.936 --> 30:13.971
[SQUEAKING]

30:29.536 --> 30:31.994
But even these clever hunters...

30:32.247 --> 30:33.453
...can't solve...

30:33.707 --> 30:35.038
...this puzzle.

30:41.548 --> 30:43.459
The mouse has no choice...

30:43.717 --> 30:46.084
...but to hold out till dusk.

31:17.876 --> 31:20.334
In the forest, the chill in the air...

31:20.587 --> 31:24.501
...spells trouble
for the smallest creatures.

31:36.937 --> 31:39.178
A tiny body gives no defense...

31:39.439 --> 31:41.350
...against the cold.

31:42.734 --> 31:44.099
[CHIRPS]

31:45.737 --> 31:46.943
There's only one way...

31:47.197 --> 31:50.531
...this young chipmunk
can survive now.

31:51.576 --> 31:53.908
He needs to find his stolen acorns...

31:54.162 --> 31:55.778
...and get them back.

32:04.589 --> 32:07.297
He's found the thief's burrow.

32:08.176 --> 32:09.792
[CHIRPING]

32:36.705 --> 32:38.742
He's caught in the act.

32:44.713 --> 32:47.205
It's flight or fight.

32:48.383 --> 32:50.374
He chooses fight.

32:52.012 --> 32:52.877
[BOTH TRILLING]

33:27.506 --> 33:29.122
[SQUEALS]

33:36.681 --> 33:38.763
[SQUEALS]

33:46.608 --> 33:48.940
The youngster's won.

33:54.032 --> 33:57.775
He can reclaim his stolen acorns...

33:58.036 --> 34:02.030
...while the thief
nurses his wounded pride.

34:03.041 --> 34:04.657
[CHIRPING]

34:40.870 --> 34:44.362
At last, his store can be returned.

34:46.333 --> 34:49.292
And not a moment too soon.

34:49.920 --> 34:52.333
Winter is here.

35:22.704 --> 35:24.615
The young chipmunk...

35:24.873 --> 35:28.036
...has made it just in time.

35:34.007 --> 35:35.998
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

35:40.096 --> 35:43.088
Sundown in the wild west.

35:46.895 --> 35:48.351
[ANIMAL HOWLING IN DISTANCE]

35:59.532 --> 36:02.274
Now is the time
for the young scorpion mouse...

36:02.535 --> 36:04.151
...to venture out.

36:20.595 --> 36:21.926
When close enough...

36:22.180 --> 36:24.262
...a lost mouse can follow its nose...

36:24.516 --> 36:25.176
...all the way...

36:25.433 --> 36:26.764
...home.

36:56.756 --> 37:00.294
There comes a time
when every youngster faces...

37:00.552 --> 37:01.587
...a difficult choice:

37:01.845 --> 37:03.461
[MICE SQUEAKING]

37:05.557 --> 37:07.093
An easy life...

37:11.146 --> 37:13.478
...or independence.

37:16.985 --> 37:19.818
Independence has its dangers.

37:26.494 --> 37:30.328
But what would life be
without a challenge?

37:32.542 --> 37:35.409
Even if it means
fighting a venomous...

37:35.670 --> 37:37.911
...two-headed monster.

37:40.592 --> 37:42.959
He closes his eyes to protect them...

37:43.219 --> 37:46.086
...but he can still see
with his whiskers.

37:47.223 --> 37:48.588
[SQUEAKING]

38:10.622 --> 38:13.580
But as they say,
what doesn't kill you...

38:13.833 --> 38:14.664
...only makes you...

38:14.918 --> 38:16.283
...stronger.

38:16.544 --> 38:18.410
[HOWLING]

38:23.051 --> 38:24.507
[MOUSE HOWLING IN DISTANCE]

38:25.804 --> 38:29.798
Their mothers give them
the start they need.

38:35.271 --> 38:36.557
But it's their own experience...

38:37.232 --> 38:39.223
...that finally makes a man...

38:39.484 --> 38:41.066
...of the mouse.

38:50.036 --> 38:51.197
He's finally ready...

38:51.454 --> 38:54.287
...to leave his home forever...

38:54.707 --> 38:58.701
...and to wander the desert alone.

39:05.802 --> 39:07.292
Compared to us...

39:07.554 --> 39:11.263
...little creatures live at breakneck speed.

39:13.560 --> 39:17.554
Their lives are brief,
but burn brightly.

40:04.986 --> 40:07.318
Here, in the temperate forest...

40:07.572 --> 40:10.189
...the big freeze sets in.

40:10.658 --> 40:11.773
[ANIMAL HOWLING IN DISTANCE]

40:15.830 --> 40:17.491
[SCREECHES]

40:18.082 --> 40:21.074
For the large animals,
this is a time...

40:21.336 --> 40:22.497
...of hardship.

40:43.816 --> 40:45.602
For a chipmunk...

40:46.110 --> 40:49.193
...it's a chance
to take a well-deserved rest.

40:49.781 --> 40:51.146
[CHIRPING]

40:52.241 --> 40:56.235
The start of six months
of peaceful sleep.

40:59.290 --> 41:01.156
And when he gets hungry...

41:01.417 --> 41:03.078
...he'll wake, briefly...

41:03.336 --> 41:06.829
...and feed on his store of acorns.

41:13.930 --> 41:15.921
Little guys don't always...

41:16.182 --> 41:18.048
...finish last.

41:23.731 --> 41:26.644
And in a land of giants...

41:26.901 --> 41:30.644
...heroes come in all sizes.

43:13.007 --> 43:14.998
[English - US - SDH]
